snippet.textDisplay:
I used to rule the world
Chunks would load when I gave the word
Now every night I go stow away
Hide from the mobs I used to slay
They once were terrified
Every time I looked into their eyes
Villagers would cheer my way
For a hero I was, that's what they'd say
One minute we had it all
Next our world began to fall
Away from all that it had once become
They all cried for my help, but I stood there numb
I gaze off into the boundless skyline
Noteblock choirs playing in the sunshine
Turn 'round pick up my sword and wield
The blade that once forced evil mobs to yield
And hope one day that this chaos and
Destruction turns for the better
Never a bow in hand
That was when I ruled the land
It was the creepers and Skeletons
Blew down the doors and boxed us in
Arrows whizzing by like streaks of light
I tried all that I could to stay and fight
As the undead roamed the street
Families broken at my feet
Life itself suspended by a thread
Oh, why is it that I wasn't dead
I gaze off into the boundless skyline
Noteblock choirs playing in the sunshine
Turn 'round pick up my sword and wield
The blade that once forced evil mobs to yield
If this battle should leave me slain
I know that Herobrine will call my name
Better to take a stand
That was when I ruled the land
I gaze off into the boundless skyline
(Noteblock choirs playing in the sunshine)
Turn 'round pick up my sword and wield
The blade that once forced evil mobs to yield
If this battle should leave me slain
I know that Herobrine will call my name
Better to take a stand
That was when I ruled the land

Ok I have an idea about the random structures:
Following your theory that Illagers are trying to create a form of life somewhat like Steve, maybe the random rooms are a source of education for the beings that are created. Cats can be tamed and used to scare away creepers. If Illagers do originate from villages they do know about them as they spawn in that area. Chickens are a common source of food, not only for their meat, but also eggs. They are also easily bred with any kind of seed, which can be found in villages. The end portal could be there to tell the beings that that is one of their goals, just like it is the players to 'complete the game'. Everything is made out of wool as it is a common material that can be in many colors. They Illagers where just trying to remake them to show the beings the general appearance of the object/being.

This theory doesn't cover a lot so it is most likely incorrect, but it's just something that came to my mind. It be cool to find some more clues to expand it.

snippet.textDisplay:
My theory was the Illagers were villagers who met the previous builders, like Steve. The builders came with gifts of tamed cats (from ocelots, like in the original Minecraft), and taught them to farm and created golems to protect the villages. However, unlike the simple villagers, Illagers were smarter, and chose to learn from the builders, thus making the mansions they now live in and learning about enchanting. They were not cast out of the villages, they abandoned the simple village life, seeking to become like the builders who could do so much more and go beyond their limits. They wanted to evolve.
But then came the day the builders vanished. Like your previous theories, they were killed off by the wither, of forced into the End, leaving their strongholds and portals empty and abandoned. The Illagers were isolated in their mansions studying and trying to evolve more to be like the builders, so they were unaware of the Wither chasing off their beloved builders. When they finally came out to seek the builders for new knowledge, they only found the empty strongholds. The Illagers had no knowledge of what anything in the strongholds were or how they worked.
Without the builders, the Illagers became distraught, knowing that they could learn nothing more without the builders. They began to obsess over finding the builders. Eventually it turned into worship. The Fake portals are basically alters to honor the builders. The Giant cat and chicken statues, and the little tree and farms in the mansions are to honor the first gifts from the Builders. But it was still not enough without the builders. The Illagers needed to bring the builders back somehow.
They brought the witches (who were outcasts from the villages for dark magic) into their fold and the envokers learned magic from them. Vindicators trained to raid and look villages of their people and resources for the Envokers to experiment on "creating" a builder. The piles of colored wool to make the clothes of the builders. The Illagers abandoned all their good moral standings, and believing their cause to be justified, started to experiment in a near Frankenstein method to create their own Builder...basically, bring their Gods back.
